For a complete description of use custom fonts in client-side, read the article: Custom fonts (client-side)
If you don&rsquo;t want to install gulp and/or just downloaded pdfMake and want to use custom fonts in client-side, you can generate the vfs_fonts.js with an bash-script as well:
#!/bin/sh  if [ -t 1 ]; then target=&#34;vfs_fonts.js&#34; else target=&#34;/dev/stdout&#34; fi ( echo -n &#34;this.pdfMake = this.pdfMake || {}; this.pdfMake.vfs = {&#34; for file in &#34;$@&#34;; do file=$1 shift echo -n &#39;&#34;&#39; echo -n &#34;$(basename $file)&#34; echo -n &#39;&#34;:&#34;&#39; echo -n &#34;$(base64 -w 0 $file)&#34; echo -n &#39;&#34;&#39; if [ &#34;$#&#34; -gt 0 ]; then echo -n &#34;,&#34; fi done echo -n &#34;};&#34; ) &gt; &#34;$target&#34; How to use script:
